		on Tuesday January 30, 2024 @12:09PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//apple.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23210140&amp;cid=64200898">#64200898</a>)
		<small><a href="https://dianne.skoll.ca/" title="https://dianne.skoll.ca/" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64200898"><p>If the Linux kernel or some other open-source project introduces new security features, how exactly could the UK government do anything about this?  Short of blocking all access to non-UK git repos, this seems impossible.</p><p>And the zeroth rule of lawmaking is: Don't make a law you can't enforce.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64200898">
